{"word":"ἱμείρω","slug":"ἱμείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἱμείρω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἵμερος'><el>ἵμερος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to long for, yearn after, desire</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to long</i> or <i>wish</i> to do, <b>Solon</b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to desire</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ὁππότ' ἂν ἧς ἱμείρεται αἴης</el> (epic for <el>-ηται</el>) <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>χρημάτων ἱμ. μεγάλως</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}